Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.51,0:00:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So the other doorway past the intellect\Nis the aesthetics, the appreciation, the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.27,0:00:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,reverence for beauty, the reverence for\Npurity and beautiness
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.00,0:00:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and to see\Nthe um
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.32,0:00:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,sacredness of all that exists.\NBecause all that exists
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.44,0:00:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of\Nits source. Then divinity is intrinsic
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.92,0:00:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that exists.\Nthe capacity to experience this divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.96,0:01:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,directly then becomes\Nuh relatively
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.92,0:01:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,innate to one's experience of\Nlife itself. So how to transcend the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.08,0:01:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,intellect? Um you can't get there via\Nadvanced theoretical physics. You can't
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.88,0:01:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,get there.\NYou can certainly
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.79,0:01:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrate its reality because\Nusing a calibration technique which we
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.36,0:01:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about you can calibrate what is the\Nlevel of that beauty and we just did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.52,0:01:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We just did it. It's quality is\Nineffable. Um we use the term beauty. We
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.32,0:01:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,use the term but that isn't the quality.\NWhat makes you you the hair stand up on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.75,0:01:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the back of your head when the violin\Nhits a certain note is a different
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.96,0:01:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,quality of consciousness\Nand it transcends the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.15,0:01:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So the traditional ways to God the the\Nupside the positive side of religion
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.43,0:02:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,has been its recognition of beauty as a\Ngreat transporter of human spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.47,0:02:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I mean. The great cathedrals\Nof the world, great cathedrals of Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.95,0:02:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,especially\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.20,0:02:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,depict probably the greatest possible\Nachievement
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.04,0:02:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind within the physical domain.\NThe uh endless lifetimes. Some of those
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.80,0:02:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,cathedrals took a thousand years to\Nbuild.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.56,0:02:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Century after century, people devoting\Ntheir entire life to just carving
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.51,0:02:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,one pulpit in 3D. And I've looked at\Npulpit that the man spend his entire
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.40,0:02:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,life. There's three levels of figures\Nwithin this pulpit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.08,0:03:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,One entire lifetime just to do that one\Ncarving.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.72,0:03:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So um we won't talk anymore about beauty\Nin a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.48,0:03:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so that is one of the great and\Ntraditional ways
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.40,0:03:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience what you might say are\Nvarious aspects
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.20,0:03:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence.\NThat which is love, that which is peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.28,0:03:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is beauty.\NNot beauty of perception, not beauty of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.64,0:03:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,artistic um\Nappreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.36,0:03:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but an awareness that one is\Nexperiencing the essence out of which
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.12,0:03:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that beauty is being perceived.\NSo devotion and it's um so traditional
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.84,0:03:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,religion has u has understood that. So\Non the one side there's the depiction of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.95,0:04:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,God as sort of a frightening monster.\NUh on the other hand there's all that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.28,0:04:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,really sustains the core and and keeps\Nit going because if there weren't any
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.51,0:04:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,truth there would collapse out of its\Nown negativity
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.79,0:04:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as you walk into a great cathedral.\NOne time I was in Cusco and uh I wasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.12,0:04:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,used to the altitude\Nand as I got off the plane I got sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.91,0:04:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a stoned feeling you know what I mean\Nlike everything was incredibly beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.19,0:04:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and I walked down the street and I could\Nsmell this incense. Wow, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.52,0:04:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible.\NAnd so I followed the incense.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.80,0:04:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The stone chilling was due to the\Nspiritual condition that I arrived at.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.00,0:04:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,arrived in Cusco in and\Nanyway this the odor of the incense is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.08,0:05:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,coming down the street\Nand so I automatically followed this
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.47,0:05:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,incense where it was coming from and it\Nwas coming from
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,uh an ancient church and the church had\Nall these altars and these altars were
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.47,0:05:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,all made of heavy silver and you could\Nsee the the prior influence on it. Um
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.08,0:05:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, um it was right before Christmas\Nand um as you got into the church, the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.36,0:05:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,incense got heavier and heavier\Nand the organ was playing um flute music
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and Peruvian flute music\Nuh type of religious music that played
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.40,0:05:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,on. So it's coming with the sound of\NIndian flutes. So, here's this
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.68,0:05:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible flute music and the incense\Nwafting through the air and it's coming
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.32,0:05:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,out of a great big kiln up near the\Nfront of the So, near the front of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.80,0:05:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,altar is this big black thing and this\Nincense is pouring out. There's stained
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.36,0:06:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,glass windows and the sunshine is coming\Nthrough the stained glass windows. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.96,0:06:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the blues and the oranges and all are\Nintersecting the clouds of incense. In
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.40,0:06:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the meantime, in the back of the room\Nare these old I can only call them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.44,0:06:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,script descriptively crrons, old old\Nbent over with long black and the black
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,thing over them and they're rocking back\Nand forth to the music and clicking
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.63,0:06:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,these coins. So as the flutes are going\Nlike this, they're clicking the coins to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.19,0:06:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the sound of the flute music and the\Nincense is surrounding everybody and the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.72,0:06:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,colored light is coming through.\NAnd because it was near Christmas, near
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.84,0:06:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the in the front of the altar, there was\Na cray. And in the cray were the divine
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.91,0:06:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,figures.\NAnd these were lighting up and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,unlighting up periodically with the\Nsound of the of the music and the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.80,0:07:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,incense. And you wondered, whoa,\Nthat's how you get beyond 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.56,0:07:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Enchantment. One becomes enchanted.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.80,0:07:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The same states arise through\Nmeditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.12,0:07:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The same states arise through mantra.\NThe idea is to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.47,0:07:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,pull back from identification with\Nthinkingness and words and the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.84,0:07:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to un to begin to sense. So\None senses that underneath the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.36,0:07:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and thought\Nis some field of awareness. Otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.28,0:07:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how would you know what you're thinking\Nor what is going on in the mind? So,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.36,0:07:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this thinkingness comes to a a stop and\None realizes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.96,0:07:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that the stunning impact of this beauty\Nrepresents the totality of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.80,0:07:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,experience. I'm only breaking it down\Ninto words now. But at that time it was
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.16,0:08:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the incense, the beauty of the music,\Nthe chanting, the the rocking of the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.16,0:08:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,people to the music, the cre with the\Nlights flickering and the sheer divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and reverence of the whole situation.\NSo reverence, the reverence for that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.87,0:08:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which is sacred,\Nreverence
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.40,0:08:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which is sacred is one of the\Ndoors that opens the way to the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.59,0:08:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,One now does things not out of duty, not\Nout of fear of consequences,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.47,0:08:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not of not out of fear of punishment by\Na negative arbitrary God. One does it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.88,0:08:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,out of one's love for truth, out of\None's devotion to lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.44,0:08:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as a quality and a way of life.\NLovingness, as we've said, is what makes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.16,0:08:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you stop and turn the beetle over on his\Nlegs
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in the alley. He lays there on his back.\NHe cannot get on his own little feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.95,0:09:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a big black\Nand something in you. Then compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.83,0:09:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So compassion takes us beyond the 500s.\NThe compassion for all that lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.95,0:09:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The compassion comes up in one of the\Nquestions today to try to complete the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.00,0:09:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of vegetarianism\Nas a spiritual quality. That's this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.44,0:09:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,week's Time magazine. The cover of Time\Nseems to anticipate what we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.36,0:09:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture here all the time, but\Nsomebody's leaking info to them. Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.80,0:09:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,vegetarianism we had brought up before\Nthat um there are many ways of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.08,0:09:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualizing it.\NIt can be merely a way of sacrificing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.08,0:09:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be what's called tapas\Nspiritual discipline not eating fish on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.39,0:09:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Friday you see was a way it can be\Nlooked at various ways as a silly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.83,0:10:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,superstition or as an ar anacross\Nan outofdate um it can be looked at many
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.72,0:10:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,ways it can also be seen as reverence uh\Nand respect for one's religious
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.72,0:10:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,religious teachers whether it's true or\Nnot then becomes irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.76,0:10:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's irrelevant whether eating fish on\NFriday is a sinner or not sinner. So
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.76,0:10:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Nthe calibrated level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.56,0:10:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the karmic consequences have to do with\Nintention.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.27,0:10:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'd say not eating meat out of\NFriday on a Friday is out of fear of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.56,0:10:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking of it as sin because in those\Ndays we all thought of it as a sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.76,0:10:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have to confess it.\Nuh is different than reverence. If you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.36,0:10:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,do that out of reverence, then it's a\Ntotally different motivation. Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.80,0:10:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so reverence then for truth uh and the\Npursuit of truth and reverence for those
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.88,0:11:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,who are equally committed to\Napproaching the seeking the truth. So
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.12,0:11:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,another way to go into the 500s is\Nreverence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.80,0:11:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Reverence the appreciation of that which\Nis sacred. So even if you don't hold it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.07,0:11:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as sacred, I hold sacred that that\Nperson holds it as sacred. So what is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,sacred to them I respect because I\Nrealize it is sacred to them
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.16,0:11:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,even though I may not be in agreement.\NThat allows us to appreciate difference
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.83,0:11:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and still respect people who think\Ndifferently than we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.56,0:11:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So the vegetarian may do so for multiple\Nreasons and it would be the motivation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.68,0:11:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,out of respect for life. It is certainly\Npart of almost every spiritual seeker's
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.60,0:11:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,um pathway at one time or another. The\Nquestion comes up a lot of these
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.60,0:12:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,questions come up. Can you have sex? Can\Nyou have a job? You know I mean the old
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.56,0:12:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,thing was renunciation right? To\Nrenounce the world renounce all these
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.27,0:12:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,things.\NThe way of non-duality is more that one
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.95,0:12:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,stays in the law in the world and merely\Nadvances in one's understanding of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.76,0:12:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Moves from perception, moves out of\Njudgmentalism,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.48,0:12:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,uh moves out of duality and perceives\Nthem as they are. As you perceive them
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.36,0:12:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,as they are, their beauty shines forth.\NSo one can do it out of respect. Uh one
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.27,0:12:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,can do it out of reverence. One can do\Nit out of love for the animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.88,0:12:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh reverence for its life. The Native\NAmerican uh solve that one very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.04,0:12:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The great white spirit of the Native\NAmerican calibrates well over 700 and is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.51,0:12:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,quite a very advanced understanding of\Ndivinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:13:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the recognition of the sacredness of\Nall life uh which leads to the prayer of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.88,0:13:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,thanking the animal and uh for and for\Nsurrendering its life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.32,0:13:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you at the level where you think\Nthat when an animal leaves its body it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.76,0:13:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,dies there would be the obstruction of\Nthinking that you're killing killing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.20,0:13:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You think I can't eat it because it\Nmeans killing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.04,0:13:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We I think in the last lecture we went\Nthrough that killing us, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.16,0:13:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just do it for those who are not\Nthere. U we have permission to ask this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.88,0:13:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in this audience resist. The animal\Ndoesn't really realize that it just
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.72,0:13:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,died. It just goes right on in its\Netheric body and doesn't even pay any
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.60,0:13:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,attention. Resist and comes back in\Nanother physical body and hardly notice
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.36,0:13:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that either. It just thinks it's one\Ndream or another dream. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.00,0:13:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right. And so when you realize that\Nthat nothing dies it uh and that nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.44,0:14:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,dies nothing can experience death\Nbecause death is not a possibility then
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.88,0:14:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't make any difference\Nthere is a certain level also of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.63,0:14:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness I never calibrated what it is\Nuh we can do it this morning which uh in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.48,0:14:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which you see each animal willingly\Nsurrenders its life physic its
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.92,0:14:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,physicality to god\NV via you. Let me see that is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.88,0:14:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, because I saw that there is a point\Nat which at which the animal ensures its
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.63,0:14:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,own\Nevolution into the oneness with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.88,0:14:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity. It sacrifices its physicality.\NFor thee, oh Lord, do I sacrifice my
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.24,0:14:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,life.\Nuh as an act of worship I surrender my
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.16,0:15:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,life to thee.\NThat is so I understand the animal soul
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.72,0:15:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in my animal soul because I'm that which\NI am is all that is in my animal soul
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.56,0:15:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,out of my love for God\Nover and over and over again. I
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.83,0:15:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,willingly\Nsurrender this physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.72,0:15:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my act of worship.\NSo as an animal, you would be depriving
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.60,0:15:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,me then of one of my forms of act of\Nworship.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.56,0:15:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how I express my love for God.\NIn the presence of God, one would if
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.16,0:15:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,asked to surrender one's physicality,\Nanybody was beyond 500
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.83,0:15:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,would become choice of the opportunity.\NIf it pleases thee, oh Lord God, this
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.88,0:16:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,physicality,\NI now surrender to thee.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.00,0:16:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NThe sacredness of the animal soul
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.16,0:16:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is not a human soul, but it all is\Ncreated by God is equally sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.83,0:16:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, so the animal then\Ncan only come into physicality
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.68,0:16:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,artificially in the numbers they do by\Nthe fact that the man breeds them. If
