Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.84,0:30:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're kidding. He missed it all\Ntogether because it wasn't of that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.20,0:30:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sufficient. You weren't focused on the\Nworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.52,0:31:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the time when the person reaches\Na very advanced level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.32,0:31:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they cease and desist from human\Nlife and affairs. The majority of people
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.96,0:31:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,who reach very advanced levels of\Nconsciousness are never heard from
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.79,0:31:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,again.\NOnly with great rarity and after
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.27,0:31:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,considerable effort is there the return\Nof the capacity to function in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.44,0:31:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,much less to master both\Nuh simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.32,0:31:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nwhat would you would say would be a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.84,0:31:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,problem would be a way in which\Nsomething is being looked at.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.55,0:31:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people see problems in situations\Nwhere I don't see any problem. As far as
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.72,0:31:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm concerned, that's just the way it\Nis. And u
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.36,0:31:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,say people kill each other and millions\Ndie. You say, "Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.55,0:32:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Shouldn't you be out there\Nparading for peace?" Well, I think
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.20,0:32:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody should, but not me.\N10 million come 10 million go. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.72,0:32:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,going to keep recycling back and forth.\N10 million more in this, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.72,0:32:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,century after century. It just goes on\Nand so you see the flow of the nature of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.96,0:32:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,life and there is no desire to try to\Nenter the river and change its course
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.20,0:32:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because the wisdom of God prevails.\NNothing escapes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.36,0:32:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what do we say the karmic unity of\Nthe unmanifest to manifest. And what it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.44,0:32:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,manifests is one karmic totality and\Nabsolutely perfectly balanced unity. And
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.91,0:32:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there is really no necessity to do\Nanything about it whatsoever because it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.72,0:32:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,evolves of its own nature because the\Nprogression of consciousness is innate
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.84,0:33:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,within the nature of consciousness\Nitself and it doesn't need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.55,0:33:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't need my help.\NThat's the thing as a teacher you have
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.84,0:33:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to go that's another whole block about\Nteaching or not teaching and the meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.12,0:33:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the significance and the value and\Nand then of course no there's nobody
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.48,0:33:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,left to teach so it either happens or it\Ndoesn't happen and it has to do with the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.36,0:33:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic coherence of\Nat a certain point one transcends
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.08,0:33:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,personal karma personal karma but one\Ndoes not transcend the the karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.39,0:33:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,intention of divinity does not escape\Nthe karmic consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.96,0:33:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the luciferic mistake of\Nselling out integrity for power over
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.27,0:33:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,others. When you see that there is no\Nnegative god that you're going to have
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.15,0:33:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to be answerable to is an error. At the\Nlevel at which that temptation comes in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.32,0:34:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is very strong. It's very cleverly and\Nconvincingly phrased and many as the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.32,0:34:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,guru has fallen for it.\Nfame and fortune and power over others.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.56,0:34:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because the lie which is\Nluciferically expressed is correct
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.76,0:34:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,within content,\Nbut it ignores the context that you've
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.56,0:34:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not escaped the karmic destiny\Nof God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.76,0:34:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have escaped your own personal\Nkarmic destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.35,0:34:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,at a certain level beyond 600. You're\Nnot really answerable for it in a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.07,0:34:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,personal way. But one is still within\Nthe karmic coherence of the talitality
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.39,0:34:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of of the context of God. So you're not\Nbeyond karma. You're only beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.20,0:34:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,personal karma. But boy, you sure are\Nwithin the powerful karmic field of the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.24,0:35:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite presence of almighty God.\NAnd that is the sad discovery. Once the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.16,0:35:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,mistake is made,\Nit is sacrificed to all for illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.72,0:35:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,God being the infinite context then is\Nthe ultimate infinite possibility of all
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.40,0:35:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists. All of which is kept within\Na karmic perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.76,0:35:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,balance. That's why you don't have to\Nfear judgment because everything comes
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.28,0:35:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,about as a result of the essence of its\Nown expressing itself within the context
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.07,0:35:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of God. It's inescapable.\NThere's no such thing as a murderer
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.20,0:35:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,getting away with it. People say, "Oh,\Nhe got away with it." Yeah, right. He
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.92,0:35:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,got away with it. Big joke of the\Ncentury. Nobody gets away with anything
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.16,0:35:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because all is noticed\Nand that's what kinesiology is based on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.20,0:36:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology is based on the inherent\Ncoherence
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.72,0:36:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which is guaranteed by its essence as\Ndivinity
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.76,0:36:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that nothing escapes\Nthe infinite allness of God and is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.68,0:36:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,registered forever with an accessible\Nfield that we call consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.59,0:36:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is the whole basis of the test\Nof kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.52,0:36:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which is registers within\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.32,0:36:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,forever.\NAll that ever is or has been
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.59,0:36:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore all truth stands revealed.\NAll truth is accessible.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.16,0:36:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that has ever happened in is\Naccessible.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.96,0:37:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our own search for spiritual truth then\Ntends to influence our family
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.07,0:37:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh for better or worse.\NThey either may think you're crazy and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.72,0:37:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,decide they're going to go in the\Nopposite direction. Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.44,0:37:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I I would say people either are not to\Nevolve look directly at an incredible
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.20,0:37:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,miracle witnessed by all kinds of people\Nnot even see it much less do they
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.72,0:37:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,understand the miraculous nature of what\Nthey just witnessed. In fact they go
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.00,0:37:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,into denial of what they just saw. It's\Nvery interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.64,0:37:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,incapacity to see the obvious. So\Npeople live in different realities. So
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.07,0:37:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what because of one's level of\Nconsciousness then what would be a
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.72,0:37:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,problem a bad habit or a neurosis would\Ndepend on what level you're at
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.92,0:37:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,any more questions about that because\Npeople do worry about uh such things
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.68,0:37:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,when you re-energize the persona in\Norder to re uh react act act be active
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.04,0:38:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with in the world the persona is\Nhabitual set set of knowing social
