Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.20,0:42:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity.\NI'm the one that was careless about
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.80,0:42:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,where I put my feet. And if you see what\NI mean, every every ding in the car, I
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.31,0:42:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,take responsibility for. I mean it was\Nmy thoughtlessness that allowed for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.28,0:42:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So that kind of training we can teach\Nour children. We can I think we can
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.72,0:42:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,inspire them to\Nuh become integrous and to feel the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.24,0:42:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,increase of power and energy that goes\Nwith integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.16,0:42:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you teach them uh by example and\Nand and keep bringing to their awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.72,0:42:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is a certain payoff in\Nself-esteem which nobody sees.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.44,0:42:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you don't have to pick it up. You\Ndon't have to pick it up. You don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.56,0:42:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to pick it up. But when you do over and\Nover again, suddenly you notice a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.80,0:43:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,difference in how you feel about\Nyourself and that's called self-esteem.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.04,0:43:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think the building of self-esteem\Nthrough integrity is something we can
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.88,0:43:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly do. You remember EST from back\Nin the 60s or 70s? I forget when was the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.07,0:43:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,'7s.\N>> Yeah. Well, what Wernner was trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.64,0:43:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,teach, I mean, he had his own problems,\Nbut aside from that, what he was trying
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.80,0:43:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to do is get everybody over 200. He\Nwanted everybody to be over integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.92,0:43:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,take responsibility,\Nthat you're creating your own
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.07,0:43:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,experience. And of course, everybody\Nwent through shock. They took away your
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.35,0:43:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,watch and your lip ice. And\Nyou couldn't go to the bathroom. You
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.76,0:43:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't eat. You couldn't drink water,\Nno tea, no coffee. It was a real big
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.28,0:43:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,shock. And people went through all kinds\Nof agonies. And it's really, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.04,0:43:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it brought up a lot of compassion. You\Nsee people lying on the lying there
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.68,0:43:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,crying and desperate because they she\Ncouldn't have her lipstick or she could,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.68,0:43:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, didn't have her watch or they\Nhad to go to the bathroom. I mean, all
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.24,0:44:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,these little trivial childhood things.\Nand they were going through these
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.96,0:44:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,horrible agonies almost, you know, going\Nthrough major crisis, major crisis,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.92,0:44:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,major nervous breakdowns over some\Nlittle habit. It's lunchtime and they're
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.80,0:44:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,not having their lunch crisis. So it was\Na very interesting experience and I
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.48,0:44:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,thought\Nthat anybody who loved their kids would
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.16,0:44:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,send them to EST, you know,\Nbecause ES could do what you couldn't do
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.76,0:44:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as a parent, you know,\Nuh it was very intense training, but you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.64,0:44:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,also learned very rapidly.\NAnd after that, you never worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.80,0:44:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,making it to the bathroom ever again.\NIf you just resist it and resist it, it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.76,0:44:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears. Now you don't have to go to\Nthe bathroom at all. Wow, that's quite a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.00,0:44:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,discovery to go through the the crisis\Nof the bladder and come out victorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.83,0:44:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to go. You had to go and if you\Ndon't go, you're going to go and you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.40,0:44:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,don't go and then suddenly all of a\Nsudden it disappears. You ever have that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.96,0:45:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,happen? It disappears. If you withstand\Nit and transcend it, a couple minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.44,0:45:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond that, you don't have to go\Nanymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.07,0:45:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we can stop now. I don't have to\Ngo anymore. So you just crossed another
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.83,0:45:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,barrier.\NSo I think those are things that we can
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.11,0:45:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,really encourage our children is\Nintegrity.
